Before We Start&hellip;
I sent Proton an email regarding this issue in late August 2022 and was told they are working on fixing it, though it will take some time as it requires some architectural changes in how the killswitch works.
The Leak Ideally, when implementing a killswitch, a VPN client should drop all connections on non-VPN interfaces except when the connection is to the VPN provider&rsquo;s servers. This is necessary to prevent accidental leaks, at least by unprivileged applications.
